{"content": "Given the sequence:\n\\[\na_n = (-1)^{n+1}(3n + 2)\n\\]\n\nWe are to find:\n\\[\nS = a_1 + a_2 + \\dots + a_{100}\n\\]\n\nLet's analyze the terms:\n\nFor odd \\( n \\):\n- \\( n+1 \\) is even, so \\( (-1)^{n+1} = 1 \\)\n- \\( a_n = 3n + 2 \\)\n\nFor even \\( n \\):\n- \\( n+1 \\) is odd, so \\( (-1)^{n+1} = -1 \\)\n- \\( a_n = -(3n + 2) \\)\n\nGroup terms in pairs: \\( (a_1 + a_2), (a_3 + a_4), \\dots, (a_{99} + a_{100}) \\)\n\n**Each pair:**\n\\[\na_{2k-1} + a_{2k} = (3(2k-1) + 2) + [-(3(2k) + 2)]\n\\]\n\\[\n= (6k - 3 + 2) - (6k + 2)\n\\]\n\\[\n= (6k - 1) - (6k + 2)\n\\]\n\\[\n= -1 - 2 = -3\n\\]\n\nThere are 50 pairs (since 100 terms):\n\n\\", "in": 102, "out": 300}